reviews.review_text: Fabulous AUD I had a cassette of this, although it sounded garble here and there i use to play it a lot, this AUD is right up there in my book! Way better sounded after the Miller touch and hats off to the taper who had the sweet spot that night. Enjoyed Bird Song and Cold Rain and Snow, The Help Slip Franklin in 83 was a treat to hear again. The Good Lovin is above average, i favor the Baby Blue encore. Ah The Grateful Dead on the East Coast, nice euphoric recall indeed!
